==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''Iason'', from ''iasthai'', (to heal).

===Proper noun===
'''Jason'''
{{wikipedia}}

# ''(Greek Mythology)'' leader of the Argonauts, who retrieved the Golden Fleece from king Aeetes of Colchis, for his uncle Pelias.
